Durban - Police in Esikhaleni, northern KwaZulu-Natal arrested three wanted men for possession of illegal firearms on Tuesday. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, police spokesperson, said police were following up on information about men in possession of illegal firearms. Zwane said the police searched a rented house and found three men in possession of three unlicensed firearms and ammunition. “Cellphones suspected to be taken during house robberies were also found in the house. On further investigation, it appeared that the suspects were wanted for a number of house and business robberies in and around Esikhaleni and Richards Bay area. All three suspects aged between 19 and 32 years were arrested and charged with possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition,” he said. He said they will appear at the Esikhaleni Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. Major General Bheki Langa, Acting Provincial Commissioner in KwaZulu-Natal, encouraged community members to work together with the police in the fight against crime by providing valuable information about criminal activities in their areas. He also said the firearms will undergo ballistic tests to establish if they were used in other crimes. Earlier in the month, KwaZulu-Natal police arrested three men for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. At the time, Colonel Thembeka Mbhele, police spokesperson had said five unlicensed firearms which are made up of two AK47’s, a 9mm pistol, a revolver with an assortment of 12 ammunition. Daily News